# Requirements and Conceptual Model
Julissa, El, Tracy
The end user is Lana. The end user will need to be able to track her clients, dogs, walks, and payments. 
Clients
-ClientID
-First Name
-Last Name
-Phone Number
-Address

Dogs
-DogID
-Dog Name
-Dog Breed
-ClientID

Walks
-WalkID
-DogID
-Date
-Time
-Duration
-Status

Payment
-PaymentID
-ClientID
-Amount
-Payment Method
-Date

#Logical Model
Tables will be: Clients, Dogs, Walks, Payments
-Client to Dogs may have a one to many relationship because one client may have more than one dog
-Dog and Walk may have a one to many relationship because one dog can have many walks
-Client to Payments may have more than one dog because one client may have many payments
-A many to many relationship could be between walks and dogs since Lana may walk multiple dogs
